1
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:34,136
(Azure Spring)

2
00:00:34,137 --> 00:00:36,772
(All characters, places, events, etc. depicted are fictional.)

3
00:00:36,773 --> 00:00:39,142
(Children and animals were filmed under strict guidelines.)

4
00:01:02,098 --> 00:01:03,099
So?

5
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,536
Any thoughts after your first harvest, baby free diver?

6
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,640
I loved it.

7
00:01:11,641 --> 00:01:13,641
So much so that I couldn't think of anything else.

8
00:01:16,446 --> 00:01:18,481
Didn't you like it a lot?

9
00:01:19,115 --> 00:01:20,116
What?

10
00:01:20,817 --> 00:01:22,484
She felt so good...

11
00:01:22,485 --> 00:01:25,655
that she took back calling me rude and even said I was like the sea.

12
00:01:26,389 --> 00:01:29,125
What? The sea?

13
00:01:29,592 --> 00:01:31,827
Darn it. Were you flirting with him?

14
00:01:31,828 --> 00:01:33,196
You said you weren't interested!

15
00:01:33,496 --> 00:01:36,131
What? Wait. No way!

16
00:01:36,132 --> 00:01:37,534
I never said...

17
00:01:38,601 --> 00:01:40,035
Keep it quiet.

18
00:01:40,036 --> 00:01:41,271
What's going on?

19
00:01:43,106 --> 00:01:44,207
Did you just smile?

20
00:01:44,474 --> 00:01:46,475
Hey!

21
00:01:46,476 --> 00:01:48,178
Where do you think you're going? Sit down.

22
00:01:48,545 --> 00:01:51,213
- What is really going on? - I swear.

23
00:01:51,214 --> 00:01:53,583
It wasn't like that.

24
00:01:54,117 --> 00:01:56,286
If it wasn't that, then what was it?

25
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,121
Jeez.

26
00:01:58,622 --> 00:02:00,923
You're smiling? Did you just smile?

27
00:02:00,924 --> 00:02:03,326
I loved that the sea was there.

28
00:02:08,898 --> 00:02:12,101
Nothing's going on. I mean it.

29
00:02:12,102 --> 00:02:14,504
Why are you doing this to me?

30
00:02:14,771 --> 00:02:17,574
- So what's going on? - Nothing!

31
00:02:17,974 --> 00:02:19,075
Did you just smile?

32
00:02:21,044 --> 00:02:23,480
- I'm done. - Come on.

33
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:32,155
(Jung Gi Tae)

34
00:02:49,239 --> 00:02:52,242
(Republic of Korea Army Park Jae Hui)

35
00:03:07,891 --> 00:03:13,897
(Episode 4: Secret of the Deep Sea)

36
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:18,468
Excuse...

37
00:03:19,769 --> 00:03:21,504
Hey, you call him out.

38
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,110
Duk Hyun, dinner's ready. Come on out.

39
00:03:38,555 --> 00:03:39,556
Sit over here.

40
00:03:46,896 --> 00:03:48,398
I don't eat anything raw.

41
00:03:49,432 --> 00:03:53,036
What? You're a free diver. How can you not eat raw seafood?

42
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:56,005
Eating seafood raw can expose you...

43
00:03:56,006 --> 00:03:58,126
- to parasites and bacterial infections... - Open up.

44
00:04:00,443 --> 00:04:01,645
Chew on it.

45
00:04:02,379 --> 00:04:04,881
You'll taste more of the ocean than when it's boiled.

46
00:04:17,661 --> 00:04:18,828
Well, it is dangerous...

47
00:04:20,764 --> 00:04:23,433
because it's so good and could get you addicted.

48
00:04:24,234 --> 00:04:25,235
Right?

49
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:31,574
Try a piece of turban snail. It's chewy and tender.

50
00:04:47,691 --> 00:04:49,392
Yes, it's good.

51
00:04:51,995 --> 00:04:53,596
- Cheers. - Cheers.

52
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:01,905
Duk Hyun.

53
00:05:04,174 --> 00:05:05,809
I look flushed, don't I?

54
00:05:08,478 --> 00:05:10,580
But why do you talk to him like he's older than you?

55
00:05:11,548 --> 00:05:12,908
You don't even know how old he is.

56
00:05:13,049 --> 00:05:14,317
Because...

57
00:05:15,118 --> 00:05:16,987
he's good-looking.

58
00:05:18,254 --> 00:05:22,125
Then should everyone who's ugly be considered younger?

59
00:05:28,231 --> 00:05:30,266
Hey, now that you're considered younger than me,

60
00:05:30,934 --> 00:05:32,369
let me ask you this.

61
00:05:33,970 --> 00:05:35,572
My dear younger friend,

62
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,880
why did you become a free diver?

63
00:05:45,915 --> 00:05:46,916
Because I can...

64
00:05:48,318 --> 00:05:49,619
be alone.

65
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,292
I must be alone.

66
00:05:55,859 --> 00:05:57,027
That's why I harvest seafood.

67
00:06:01,031 --> 00:06:02,098
It was unexpected.

68
00:06:03,466 --> 00:06:05,368
I thought I had a grasp of who he was.

69
00:06:07,137 --> 00:06:09,906
A lonely man's elegant hobby.

70
00:06:14,911 --> 00:06:16,413
That's way too sexy.

71
00:06:17,147 --> 00:06:19,716
He's so fatally charming.

72
00:06:20,116 --> 00:06:22,285
Hey. Go home, Su Jeong.

73
00:06:22,652 --> 00:06:23,653
You're drunk.

74
00:06:25,956 --> 00:06:28,124
It's way too late for me to go home alone.

75
00:06:29,259 --> 00:06:31,393
- Can you walk me home... - Have a safe walk back.

76
00:06:31,394 --> 00:06:32,996
What? Duk Hyun...

77
00:06:35,732 --> 00:06:37,100
Wait, Duk Hyun!

78
00:06:39,002 --> 00:06:40,603
He may be much darker and deeper,

79
00:06:41,371 --> 00:06:42,539
just like...

80
00:06:43,173 --> 00:06:44,641
the deep sea.

81
00:06:52,515 --> 00:06:53,683
Jeez.

82
00:06:54,117 --> 00:06:57,120
I wanted to walk home with Duk Hyun.

83
00:06:57,821 --> 00:07:00,101
Why are you interested in someone you know nothing about?

84
00:07:00,757 --> 00:07:02,392
What if he's dangerous?

85
00:07:03,226 --> 00:07:05,095
I've known him for three years now.

86
00:07:05,362 --> 00:07:08,964
He's been quietly harvesting food not for one or two years,

87
00:07:08,965 --> 00:07:11,501
but three whole years. No way he's dangerous.

88
00:07:11,935 --> 00:07:15,472
That's why all the rumours have disappeared.

89
00:07:16,106 --> 00:07:17,907
There were rumours about him?

90
00:07:18,475 --> 00:07:20,076
So many of them.

91
00:07:20,410 --> 00:07:22,545
Some said he was an agent who left in disgrace,

92
00:07:22,946 --> 00:07:24,906
others that he was a murderer just out of prison,

93
00:07:25,181 --> 00:07:28,718
or a hidden child of a conglomerate family, and many more.

94
00:07:29,252 --> 00:07:33,356
At first, he was an extremely suspicious man.

95
00:07:34,024 --> 00:07:35,091
But now...

96
00:07:39,329 --> 00:07:40,363
Suspicious.

97
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:48,438
He seems...

98
00:07:50,573 --> 00:07:51,574
very suspicious.

99
00:07:52,008 --> 00:07:53,009
Yes.

100
00:08:02,252 --> 00:08:03,552
- Who is that? - Darn it.

101
00:08:03,553 --> 00:08:05,054
I've never seen him before.

102
00:08:05,055 --> 00:08:06,056
Jeez.

103
00:08:10,226 --> 00:08:11,861
No, don't go. Watch out.

104
00:08:17,901 --> 00:08:20,737
Darn it. Where is it?

105
00:08:24,608 --> 00:08:25,709
Jeez.

106
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:56,906
Did he start a family with a free diver, or did he become one?

107
00:08:57,207 --> 00:08:58,241
What the heck?

108
00:09:26,336 --> 00:09:27,616
What's he going to do with that?

109
00:09:28,471 --> 00:09:29,639
Wait, is he...

110
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,908
a robber?

111
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:36,279
- No way. - Where are you, Yoon Duk Hyun?

112
00:09:38,515 --> 00:09:39,549
No!

113
00:09:39,783 --> 00:09:40,884
Hey, be quiet.

114
00:09:42,619 --> 00:09:43,720
He must be...

115
00:09:44,354 --> 00:09:46,890
someone who holds a grudge against Duk Hyun.

116
00:09:47,924 --> 00:09:50,694
I think he's here to kill him. What do we do?

117
00:09:51,227 --> 00:09:52,529
What are we going to do?

118
00:09:53,263 --> 00:09:54,397
What now?

119
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:57,634
Hey, you punk!

120
00:10:01,171 --> 00:10:02,305
Who the heck are you?

121
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:05,275
Get out of my place!

122
00:10:07,077 --> 00:10:09,145
- My goodness. - You!

123
00:10:10,046 --> 00:10:11,081
What the heck?

124
00:10:16,419 --> 00:10:17,420
What on earth?

125
00:10:20,023 --> 00:10:21,291
Seo An Na!

126
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,028
An Na!

127
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:39,242
You're up.

128
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:42,212
What happened?

129
00:10:42,646 --> 00:10:44,446
I thought you had fainted after falling,

130
00:10:44,447 --> 00:10:46,287
but you began to snore, so I moved you inside.

131
00:10:48,084 --> 00:10:49,352
Oh, thanks.

132
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:53,555
But a suspicious guy grabbed a hook,

133
00:10:53,556 --> 00:10:55,492
- trying to kill... - Are you talking about me?

134
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,328
Yes, I'm talking about him!

135
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,532
I warned you. Get lost.

136
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:07,704
I wouldn't be here now if I were scared of your warning.

137
00:11:11,441 --> 00:11:13,108
Are you two acquainted?

138
00:11:13,109 --> 00:11:14,277
- No. - Yes.

139
00:11:14,844 --> 00:11:15,845
Excuse me?

140
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:19,549
We are acquainted. He's just pouting.

141
00:11:20,784 --> 00:11:24,788
Anyway, why do you keep talking casually with me?

142
00:11:25,322 --> 00:11:27,157
What? Are you older than me?

143
00:11:29,726 --> 00:11:30,727
It looks like it.

144
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:35,565
Yes, I'm older. So what?

145
00:11:36,633 --> 00:11:38,768
I'm casual with anyone within a ten-year age gap.

146
00:11:43,273 --> 00:11:45,374
Why do you do that, hiding on an island like this?

147
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:46,476
Mind your own business.

148
00:11:47,177 --> 00:11:48,345
"Mind your own business."

149
00:11:49,045 --> 00:11:51,313
Why? Do you want to get better at diving...

150
00:11:51,314 --> 00:11:52,882
and flee overseas?

151
00:11:53,917 --> 00:11:55,251
Learn to drive a ship instead.

152
00:11:57,587 --> 00:11:58,588
"Flee"?

153
00:11:58,888 --> 00:12:00,090
You didn't know?

154
00:12:01,091 --> 00:12:03,293
He came here to avoid me and...

155
00:12:04,928 --> 00:12:05,962
Enough is enough.

156
00:12:10,066 --> 00:12:11,906
Aren't you going to grab your harvesting gear?

157
00:12:12,135 --> 00:12:13,136
Me?

158
00:12:13,336 --> 00:12:14,738
Were you going to quit after a day?

159
00:12:15,538 --> 00:12:16,573
Whatever suits you.

160
00:12:18,008 --> 00:12:20,010
Why is he taking this out on me?

161
00:12:20,443 --> 00:12:21,645
Hey, wait up!

162
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:39,462
Did you do something wrong where you came from?

163
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,463
He said you fled, so I just...

164
00:12:41,464 --> 00:12:42,532
Do I seem different now?

165
00:12:43,099 --> 00:12:44,167
It's kind of odd.

166
00:12:44,701 --> 00:12:46,503
And I got curious, too.

167
00:12:52,175 --> 00:12:53,776
Who I was or what I did doesn't change...

168
00:12:53,777 --> 00:12:56,579
the fact that I'm your tenant and diving teacher.

169
00:12:58,581 --> 00:13:00,984
Well, that's true.

170
00:13:01,184 --> 00:13:02,218
Then let's hurry.

171
00:13:02,919 --> 00:13:04,487
We have to go far today to get oysters.

172
00:13:09,826 --> 00:13:11,861
Does simply knowing someone through and through...

173
00:13:12,996 --> 00:13:14,197
create trust?

174
00:13:27,777 --> 00:13:28,912
If that were the case,

175
00:13:30,213 --> 00:13:31,915
I would've had faith in myself first.

176
00:13:37,687 --> 00:13:39,956
You can start again now.

177
00:13:47,330 --> 00:13:48,331
Trust...

178
00:13:49,432 --> 00:13:50,967
does not come from knowledge.

179
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:55,839
Maybe the reason I chase after him...

180
00:13:56,673 --> 00:13:59,276
is to find out when that trust will come.

181
00:14:02,312 --> 00:14:03,313
Oysters?

182
00:14:03,947 --> 00:14:06,950
He can find oysters in the middle of summer?

183
00:14:09,719 --> 00:14:10,854
Wait up!

184
00:14:24,768 --> 00:14:26,236
We have to get on a boat?

185
00:14:39,582 --> 00:14:41,151
I'm here, Duk Hyun!

186
00:14:42,485 --> 00:14:45,021
- What's going on? - Are you coming too, Su Jeong?

187
00:14:45,355 --> 00:14:47,457
I'd follow Duk Hyun anywhere.

188
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:50,493
Everybody is here now.

189
00:14:50,961 --> 00:14:52,462
Dad, we're good to go!

190
00:14:54,597 --> 00:14:56,967
Hang on tightly. We're off!

191
00:14:58,101 --> 00:14:59,135
Wait!

192
00:15:04,474 --> 00:15:06,443
Are you coming, too?

193
00:15:08,144 --> 00:15:09,145
We're friends after all.

194
00:15:21,558 --> 00:15:22,792
Let's go!

195
00:16:14,678 --> 00:16:16,379
How far are we going?

196
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,515
We're almost there.

197
00:16:20,884 --> 00:16:22,319
I can't do this anymore.

198
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:52,440
The Black Snake Unit's Water Ghost still got his game.

199
00:16:56,286 --> 00:16:57,320
Duk Hyun,

200
00:16:57,754 --> 00:16:59,089
I'm dizzy.

201
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:01,958
We have to get to that side.

202
00:17:02,826 --> 00:17:04,427
What? No way...

203
00:17:40,397 --> 00:17:41,398
Oh, gosh.

204
00:17:46,369 --> 00:17:47,370
An Na.

205
00:17:48,571 --> 00:17:51,808
Doesn't Duk Hyun seem suspicious?

206
00:17:53,443 --> 00:17:55,445
Didn't you call him sexy and mysterious before?

207
00:17:55,845 --> 00:17:57,080
It's not that.

208
00:17:57,981 --> 00:18:00,750
Ever since that new guy came,

209
00:18:01,251 --> 00:18:03,286
his face hasn't been the same.

210
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:05,021
I can tell just by looking at him.

211
00:18:10,126 --> 00:18:11,161
Maybe you're right.

212
00:18:12,762 --> 00:18:14,030
I'm telling you.

213
00:18:14,965 --> 00:18:16,066
Something's fishy.

214
00:18:46,496 --> 00:18:47,497
What's going on?

215
00:18:59,643 --> 00:19:00,644
Is this it?

216
00:19:01,311 --> 00:19:02,511
Is this where the oysters are?

217
00:19:05,382 --> 00:19:07,550
We must cross over to that island to harvest oysters.

218
00:19:12,022 --> 00:19:13,223
But this is the sea.

219
00:19:13,657 --> 00:19:15,458
How are we going to get there?

220
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:19,963
If we wait, the sea will open a path for us.

221
00:19:20,897 --> 00:19:23,633
Jeez, are we waiting for the miracle of Moses?

222
00:19:24,901 --> 00:19:26,202
Enough with your nonsense.

223
00:19:26,836 --> 00:19:27,837
Hey.

224
00:19:29,372 --> 00:19:30,840
Let's go over there and look around.

225
00:19:32,509 --> 00:19:36,078
What? But I want to stay here.

226
00:19:36,079 --> 00:19:37,080
Come.

227
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:38,682
Duk Hyun...

228
00:20:07,377 --> 00:20:08,645
How's your shoulder?

229
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,381
How did you know?

230
00:20:13,717 --> 00:20:17,120
You said it in your sleep at the public clinic last time...

231
00:20:19,022 --> 00:20:22,292
that your shoulder is fully healed, but you don't think you can swim again.

232
00:20:26,463 --> 00:20:27,597
Oh, gosh.

233
00:20:33,336 --> 00:20:34,404
You're right.

234
00:20:35,972 --> 00:20:37,073
To be honest,

235
00:20:38,441 --> 00:20:39,643
I'm not unwell.

236
00:20:42,212 --> 00:20:43,980
I was fine while harvesting seafood,

237
00:20:45,882 --> 00:20:46,962
and even the doctor said...

238
00:20:47,684 --> 00:20:49,786
I could go back to swimming ages ago.

239
00:20:53,923 --> 00:20:56,393
- I know, but... - But faith...

240
00:20:57,827 --> 00:20:59,329
doesn't come from knowledge.

241
00:21:04,501 --> 00:21:05,502
Then...

242
00:21:07,470 --> 00:21:08,638
what can I do...

243
00:21:10,106 --> 00:21:11,841
to have faith in myself?

244
00:21:17,681 --> 00:21:19,516
Give yourself time...

245
00:21:21,818 --> 00:21:23,753
until you can learn to trust yourself again.

246
00:21:28,858 --> 00:21:29,893
All things...

247
00:21:30,393 --> 00:21:31,761
need time.

248
00:21:45,141 --> 00:21:46,242
It opened up.

249
00:21:48,478 --> 00:21:50,947
The sea opened up!

250
00:22:17,307 --> 00:22:19,342
What? It really...

251
00:22:20,343 --> 00:22:21,344
opened up.

252
00:22:24,681 --> 00:22:25,682
Let's go.

253
00:22:29,286 --> 00:22:30,387
- Let's go. - Okay.

254
00:23:00,483 --> 00:23:01,763
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

255
00:23:09,225 --> 00:23:11,995
The sea will be different from the one we dived in last time.

256
00:23:18,101 --> 00:23:19,102
I can tell.

257
00:23:19,836 --> 00:23:21,204
It must be quite deep.

258
00:23:22,038 --> 00:23:23,373
It's very deep and dark.

259
00:23:24,941 --> 00:23:25,942
Stick out your hand.

260
00:23:31,848 --> 00:23:33,450
That's how far you can see.

261
00:23:34,818 --> 00:23:35,919
Then...

262
00:23:36,453 --> 00:23:37,854
how do you harvest seafood?

263
00:23:39,489 --> 00:23:40,490
By faith.

264
00:23:43,193 --> 00:23:44,753
Trust the training you've had so far...

265
00:23:45,795 --> 00:23:46,830
and...

266
00:23:47,430 --> 00:23:49,566
the memories from your previous diving experiences.

267
00:25:37,474 --> 00:25:38,475
But...

268
00:25:39,309 --> 00:25:40,810
can we really find oysters here?

269
00:25:55,825 --> 00:25:59,229
Rock oysters only live in the far and deep sea.

270
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:05,969
Is it like a legend?

271
00:26:08,905 --> 00:26:13,176
I wouldn't call it a legend, but more like a dream.

272
00:26:14,411 --> 00:26:15,512
The dream of free divers.

273
00:26:20,684 --> 00:26:23,386
Is there a difference between the two?

274
00:26:25,655 --> 00:26:26,723
A dream...

275
00:26:30,226 --> 00:26:32,228
can come true, as long as you believe in it.

276
00:26:58,521 --> 00:27:01,925
Faith does not come from knowledge.

277
00:27:48,338 --> 00:27:49,339
Perhaps faith...

278
00:27:50,407 --> 00:27:51,975
is born out of uncertainty.

279
00:28:32,716 --> 00:28:34,196
- Thank you for the food! - Enjoy it!

280
00:28:34,884 --> 00:28:36,753
All right. Cheers!

281
00:28:39,889 --> 00:28:41,091
Come on, Duk Hyun.

282
00:28:41,524 --> 00:28:43,927
One more time. Cheers.

283
00:28:46,596 --> 00:28:47,697
- Cheers. - Cheers.

284
00:28:56,539 --> 00:28:58,041
These look so good.

285
00:29:14,257 --> 00:29:15,325
How long...

286
00:29:16,293 --> 00:29:18,028
do you plan to stay?

287
00:29:18,695 --> 00:29:19,696
Well,

288
00:29:20,163 --> 00:29:21,364
until my business is done.

289
00:29:22,198 --> 00:29:23,300
Exactly.

290
00:29:23,733 --> 00:29:25,702
What's this business of yours?

291
00:29:27,237 --> 00:29:29,238
Duk Hyun must have...

292
00:29:29,239 --> 00:29:32,442
stolen your girlfriend, new guy.

293
00:29:33,810 --> 00:29:36,513
The war of love.

294
00:29:37,914 --> 00:29:39,983
I guess it's similar.

295
00:29:40,617 --> 00:29:43,186
What? Is that really the issue?

296
00:29:46,623 --> 00:29:48,158
This punk, Yoon Duk Hyun,

297
00:29:51,995 --> 00:29:54,264
did take something very precious from me.

298
00:30:04,307 --> 00:30:05,675
I'm calling it a night.

299
00:30:06,743 --> 00:30:08,278
Wait, Duk Hyun.

300
00:30:16,086 --> 00:30:17,787
New guy, you just made this...

301
00:30:18,888 --> 00:30:20,023
so boring.

302
00:30:20,557 --> 00:30:21,558
What now?

303
00:30:22,792 --> 00:30:23,793
So?

304
00:30:24,527 --> 00:30:26,162
What did he take from you?

305
00:30:28,398 --> 00:30:29,432
Do you want to know?

306
00:30:37,741 --> 00:30:40,210
- It's a secret. - Darn it.

307
00:30:41,478 --> 00:30:42,545
Drink as a penalty.

308
00:30:43,747 --> 00:30:45,681
Chug it down. You have to drink it in one go.

309
00:30:45,682 --> 00:30:48,017
- How am I going to do that? - Bottoms up!

310
00:30:48,018 --> 00:30:49,786
You're so tacky.

311
00:30:49,953 --> 00:30:51,453
Your hair's worse.

312
00:30:51,454 --> 00:30:54,190
- Cheers! - Darn it. What do you know about hairstyles?

313
00:31:15,946 --> 00:31:19,215
Man, that stubborn punk.

314
00:31:26,356 --> 00:31:29,225
Is he seriously harvesting oysters in the middle of summer?

315
00:31:36,433 --> 00:31:39,736
You must be thinking I'd leave after you wear me out.

316
00:31:41,471 --> 00:31:42,639
But that won't happen.

317
00:31:44,341 --> 00:31:46,276
Why are you so obsessed with me?

318
00:31:48,578 --> 00:31:49,579
I don't know.

319
00:31:50,413 --> 00:31:53,316
I forgot the reason after three years of chasing.

320
00:31:54,517 --> 00:31:57,120
All I want to do is grab you and take you with me.

321
00:31:59,322 --> 00:32:00,457
I feel the same way.

322
00:32:02,425 --> 00:32:03,727
You asked why I'm doing this,

323
00:32:04,594 --> 00:32:06,162
hiding on an island like this.

324
00:32:11,935 --> 00:32:15,105
I started because I thought that after three years,

325
00:32:17,540 --> 00:32:19,376
I might forget why I began.

326
00:32:25,448 --> 00:32:26,916
But it hasn't worked for me yet.

327
00:33:01,952 --> 00:33:03,486
Hey, Duk Hyun.

328
00:33:05,689 --> 00:33:06,723
Are you asleep?

329
00:33:08,858 --> 00:33:11,161
Stop pretending like you're asleep.

330
00:33:14,931 --> 00:33:16,199
About Jae Hui.

331
00:33:18,902 --> 00:33:19,970
We may...

332
00:33:23,239 --> 00:33:24,307
never get to see...

333
00:33:25,642 --> 00:33:27,043
Jae Hui again.

334
00:33:32,048 --> 00:33:33,216
So...

335
00:33:35,752 --> 00:33:37,854
you should stop doing this.

336
00:33:41,591 --> 00:33:44,094
Come with me to see Jae Hui. Please!

337
00:33:47,864 --> 00:33:49,032
What was that?

338
00:33:49,799 --> 00:33:51,368
Why is he screaming?

339
00:34:04,514 --> 00:34:08,351
Darn it. Doing this here won't bring back...

340
00:34:12,822 --> 00:34:14,691
that punk you killed.

341
00:34:18,528 --> 00:34:19,562
So...

342
00:34:20,563 --> 00:34:21,898
it's time to stop this.

343
00:34:23,700 --> 00:34:25,368
Come back with me.

344
00:34:28,505 --> 00:34:29,506
Please?

345
00:34:33,877 --> 00:34:35,078
Darn it.

346
00:34:41,251 --> 00:34:42,419
That guy...

347
00:34:44,988 --> 00:34:46,756
killed someone?

348
00:34:59,970 --> 00:35:00,971
Darn it.
